doc.after: Christchurch is a distinctly English city however it contains various European elements with strong Gothic Revival architecture As early settlers of New Zealand M ori culture is also prevalent in the city It features many public open spaces and parks river beds and cafes and restaurants situated in the city centre and surrounding suburbs
